Rescue services have recovered the body of a five-year-old girl after she drowned in the Umvoti River in KwaZulu-Natal at the weekend. IPSS Medical Rescue spokesperson Paul Herbst said the  child was playing  next to the river when she lost her footing and fell into the water. Herbst said she was swept downstream. He said IPSS Medical Rescue, together with police divers, the K9 unit and the National Sea Rescue Institute (NSRI) searched the river using a drone and inflatable rafts. Herbst said the child’s body  was  recovered approximately 3km downstream from where she entered the water. “We remind  everyone to exercise heightened caution around bodies of water and flowing water.” TimesLIVE